285 g Shrimp
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
56 g Snow Peas
4.5 g Moo Shu Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Green Onion
¼ cup Vegetarian Oyster Sauce
4 g Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend
28 g Crispy Shallots
1 tbsp Butter*
½ tsp Sugar*
½ tbsp Oil*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high.
Trim snow peas.
Thinly slice green onions.

To a medium bowl, add oyster sauce, half the Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1/3 cup (1/2 cup) water. Whisk to combine.
Using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp, then pat dry with paper towels.

Heat a large non-stick pan over high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Swirl pan until melted.
Add shrimp, half the Moo Shu Spice Blend (use all for 4 servings) and remaining Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend. Cook for 2-3 min, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are opaque.**
Transfer shrimp to a plate.

Heat the same pan over medium.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, snow peas and coleslaw cabbage mix. Cook for 2-3 min, stirring often, until tender crisp.
Meanwhile, to the boiling water, add noodles. Cook for 1-3 min, stirring occasionally, until tender but still firm to the bite.
Strain and rinse noodles with warm water.

To pan with veggies, add oyster sauce mixture, noodles and shrimp. Cook for 1-2 min, stirring often, until noodles are coated.
Divide noodles between bowls.
Sprinkle crispy shallots and green onions over top.